<TITLE> War crimes tribunal by next month </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 16 (bdnews24.com)  The government will complete setting up all infrastructures including docks by February to begin the trial of the 1971 war criminals, the law minister said on Tuesday. "The government is making all out efforts to complete the process appropriately and in accordance with international laws," Shafique Ahmed told reporters at the Secretariat. He said the setting up of docks in the first building of the Old High Court, the designated venue to hold the trial, would be completed by February. Ahmed said the investigation agency and panel of prosecutors would be formed at the first week of March. The government passed an act in the first session of parliament to hold the trial for war crimes. Earlier, visiting Japan International Cooperation Agency (JICA) director general Masakata Nakahara met the law minister. b
